sentences: Adriana Livia Opriș (born 17 September 1996), known professionally as Olivia Addams, is a Romanian singer, songwriter, music producer, YouTuber, TikToker and member of the band Jealous Friend.
She gained the greatest popularity in 2020 after releasing the single "Dumb".
In 2020 she won the award for best new artist at The Artist Awards, an annual music event held in Romania, organized by Big Events in partnership with the Romanian Opera Craiova.

section: == Life and career == | === 1996–2017: Childhood years. The first musical activities ===

sentences: In 2018 Olivia Addams appeared in Pete Kingsman's single "Love Poison".
The song did not get into any charts, but it was listened to on Spotify more than 750,000 times by 2020.
In 2019 the singer recorded her first solo single, called "Sick Lullaby".
In the same year, she joined the Jealous Friend band, with whom in 2019 she recorded three songs: "Who's Gonna Love You" (with Jesse Zagata), "In My Mind", and "Cold".
Olivia Addams' first single in 2020 was "I'm Lost" and was followed by her most popular song, "Dumb".
In August 2020, it released the single "Fish in the Sea", which did not gain much popularity.
In November 2020, she released a single "Are We There?" through which the awareness-raising efforts and the fight against bullying continue.
In December 2020, she released a Christmas single entitled "Merry Tik Tok" with the Romanian singer Emil Rengle.
On April 16, 2021, Olivia Addams released the single "Stranger" through Global Records and Creator Records.
In the preview on April 12, 2021, the song was broadcast on the Polish radio stations RMF FM, Radio ZET and Radio Eska.
Also, in April 2021, she released the single "Believe" with the Jealous Friend band.
In May 2021, Addams was invited to Poland.
On June 24, 2021, she released together with the Romanian band Akcent the single "Heart Attack".

After the Best New Artist Award won in 2020 at The Artist Awards, Olivia Addams was also nominated in 2021 for two categories ("Best Artist of the Future" and "International Breakthrough") and won the award for "Best Artist on TikTok".

In August 2020, she began publishing on the TikTok app, where it became very popular.
